Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

Turkmenistan has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Turkmenistan, see Return to the UK
Travel restrictions
All international scheduled commercial flights to/from Turkmenistan have been suspended. All road borders are closed. The International Seaport of Turkmenistan at Turkmenbashi is closed to passenger traffic.
There are restrictions on road travel within Turkmenistan. Traffic police check points have been established around major population centres, including Ashgabat, and road users may be subject to temperature screening.
Internal air and rail passengers may also be subject to temperature checks.
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy on +993 12 36 34 62/64.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
